Tests:
You can run pydoc ./<tests>.py  to get detailed description

All tests need to be run with root privileges

Tests:

 1. getver.py           - Get firmware version via MKHI.
 2. getver2.py          - Get firmware version via 2 connections to MKHI.
 3. getver_fixed.py     - Get firmware version via fixed address MKHI client.
 4. stress_ver.py       - Get firmware version in loop (2000 iterations.
 5. stress_byte.py      - Send single byte to a firmware client in loop (2000 iterations.
 6. stress_max.py       - Send MTU buffer to a firmware client in loop (2000 iterations.
 7. connect_all_dyn.py  - Connect all dynamic address clients and send single byte.
 8. opencnt.py          - Check possible number of opened file handles.
 9. amt_getver.py       - Get firmware version via AMTHIF.
10. amt_getver_multi.py - Get firmware version via AMTHIF using 10 connections.
.
Unit testing:
.
11. getver_ut.py        - Use python unittest framework to report test results (WIP).
12. dev_state_ut.py     - Unittest to check that driver is alive and kicking (via debugfs).
13. amt_getver_ut.py    - Unittest to get firmware version via AMTHIF.
14. connum_ut.py        - Unittest to connect to all available connections.
15. maxconn_ut.py       - Unittest to check number of open handle restrictions
